# {{lb|fr|colloquial}} great pain
#: {{ux|fr|Cette entorse me fait un '''mal de chien''', j'espère que ça va passer.|This sprain '''hurts like hell'''; I hope it gets better.}}
# {{lb|fr|colloquial}} great difficulty
#: {{ux|fr|J'ai eu un '''mal de chien''' à trouver ce livre, donc ne le perds pas!|I had a '''hell of a job''' finding that book, so don't lose it!}}

====Usage notes====
* Almost always used with undefinite article "un", often in verbal expressions such as "faire un mal de chien", "avoir un mal de chien".

====See also====
* {{l|fr|malade comme un chien}}

